(secondQuint)Study of GNS561 in Patients With Liver Cancer.

 This is a multicenter, open-label, uncontrolled, repeat-dose Phase 1/2a study designed to evaluate the safety profile and to determine the recommended Phase 2 dose of GNS561 in patients with advanced malignancies such as HCC.

 This study will enroll approximately 50 patients and consists of 2 parts: Phase 1(dose escalation) and Phase 2 (continuation).

 All patients will be treated until the occurrence of an unacceptable toxicity, disease progression, or withdrawal of consent.

 In this study a treatment cycle is defined as 4 weeks (28 days).

 Patients are to take their assigned dose of GNS561, at the same time each Monday, Wednesday and Friday following a meal.

